net.proteusframework.ui.search

Class SearchUIImpl.Options

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.search.SearchUIImpl.Options
  • Enclosing class:
    SearchUIImpl

    public static final class SearchUIImpl.Options
extends Object
    Options for the SearchUI.

    If no limits are specified, the SearchUI will use a QLRowDataModel.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

      • setSearchSuppliers

        public SearchUIImpl.Options setSearchSuppliers(List<SearchSupplier> searchSuppliers)
        Set the search suppliers.

        Required.

        If no limits are specified on the SearchModel, the SearchUI will use a QLRowDataModel.

        If multiple SearchSuppliers are configured, then the SearchUI will allow switching between them. Another option is to create multiple SearchUIImpls. See SearchUIApp.addSearchUI(TabItemDisplay, SearchUI) for that method.
        Parameters:
        searchSuppliers - the search suppliers.
        Returns:
        this.

      • setSearchSuppliersLabel

        public SearchUIImpl.Options setSearchSuppliersLabel(LocalizedText searchSuppliersLabel)
        Set the search suppliers label. This is the label for the selection UI when multiple SearchSuppliers are configured. Defaults to null.
        Parameters:
        searchSuppliersLabel - the search suppliers label.
        Returns:
        this.

      • setShowDefaultSelectionWidgets

        public SearchUIImpl.Options setShowDefaultSelectionWidgets(boolean showDefaultSelectionWidgets)
        Set the show default selection widgets flag. This causes the result view to show the MIWT default selection widgets flag. By default the selection widgets are shown if the SearchModel has bulk actions. This is not used for most SearchUIs.
        Parameters:
        showDefaultSelectionWidgets - the show default selection widgets flag.
        Returns:
        this.
